news.title: Aurum PropTech posts net loss of Rs 33.37 crore in FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 284.98 crore in 2024-25 from Rs 233.07 crore in the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing on Friday.

news.title: ED raids multiple locations in Goa over Rs 1,000 crore land scam
news.para: According to ED, these properties, originally owned by individuals and family estates, were unlawfully sold without their consent, causing serious financial and legal distress to such victims.

news.title: Mumbai: MHADA cuts RR charges for additional area for tenants of old cessed buildings
news.para: This relief will be applied retrospectively to beneficiaries declared eligible in the December 2023 lottery. Jaiswal has directed that a new policy framework be finalized by April 28, 2025.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to revive old layouts without development charges
news.para: This move is expected to benefit around 870 promoters who had proposed to develop real estate ventures on over 8,500 acres of land. The old layout permissions had been pending with the govt due to the failure of payment of development charges.

news.title: Kolkata slums to come under Thika Tenancy Act: Mayor
news.para: ​Some slums were allegedly being set on fire purposely to help these land sharks meet their goals, sources claimed. Two such cases were reported in the Bhowanipore neighbourhoods in recent months.

news.title: Jaipur development body to issue e-leases in 30 days
news.para: A JDA official stated, "The newly established guideline outlines 23 steps and allocates a specific number of mandatory days for each official engaged in the procedure to fulfil their individual responsibilities."

news.title: NCLAT halts insolvency proceedings against Ansal Group
news.para: Appearing before NCLAT on April 15 and 17, Singh argued that the buyers' voices were ignored in the insolvency process. On Apr 25, the tribunal issued a key interim order.

news.title: Goa RERA directs Raj Housing Development to refund corpus amount to housing society with interest
news.para: Goa RERA found that the builder misused the corpus fund, for which the company was directed to also pay 11.1% interest on the corpus amount.

news.title: Property transactions up 5% in Nashik in FY25
news.para: The stamp duty on property transactions is 5% across the state, while a 1% local body cess is charged on property transactions within the jurisdiction of the civic limits.

news.title: Odisha government to construct one lakh houses under rural house scheme in phase II: Minister
news.para: In the initial phase, orders have been issued for building 60,000 houses under the scheme, Panchayati Raj and Drinking Water Minister Rabi Narayan Naik said here on Friday.

news.title: Mahindra Lifesapces' profit rises 19% to Rs 85 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Total income rose marginally to Rs 55.44 crore in January-March period of the last fiscal from Rs 54.60 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: China's Country Garden sells 11% stake in LandSpace for $180 million
news.para: The disposal is part of the embattled property developer's effort to resolve its liquidity issues. Country Garden said it expects to record a cumulative pre-tax profit of 370 million yuan.

news.title: Holcim posts operating profit of $619 million in Q1 2025
news.para: Holcim posted recurring operating profit of 515 million Swiss francs ($619 million) for the three months ended March 31, beating forecasts for 494 million francs in a company-compiled consensus.

news.title: Excess property tax paid will be adjusted in next financial year: Chandigarh administration
news.para: The excess amount will instead be adjusted in the 2026-2027 financial year's property tax bills for those who paid the tax as per the previous increased rates, UT officials said.

news.title: Proptimes Consultancy Services targets ₹2,000 crore in property sales for FY 2025–26, expands operations to the UAE
news.para: Founded in 2021 by Kian Kumar, Proptimes was established with a mission to make real estate transactions more transparent, efficient, and consumer-centric.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance cuts lending rate by 25 bps
news.para: ​This reduction in LIC Housing Prime Lending Rate (LHPLR), will benefit both existing and new borrowers by making home loans more affordable, the LIC subsidiary said in a statement.

news.title: GIC partners with SAMHI Hotels for $300 million hospitality platform in India
news.para: The venture is backed by an equity infusion plan of up to $300 million, with GIC acquiring a significant minority stake in the asset-owning SPVs. SAMHI Hotels will manage both operational and under-development assets within the joint venture.

news.title: Haryana freezes circle rates amid soaring property prices
news.para: The Haryana government has decided not to make any increase in the circle rate — in a move that is likely to stabilise the overheated property market in the city and adjoining areas.
